data: Right: Biologists can study life at multiple levels of organization,[1] from the molecular biology of a cell to the anatomy and physiology of plants and animals, and the evolution of populations.[1][6] Hence, there are multiple subdisciplines within biology, each defined by the nature of their research questions and the tools that they use.[7][8][9] Like other scientists, biologists use the scientific method
